records.addlTxt:
The State moves to delete the domestic violence enhancer on counts 2, 4 and 5.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 2, operate firearm while intoxicated.  Convicted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 4, criminal damage to property. Convicted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 5, disorderly conduct. Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1 and 3; 1st degree recklessly endangering safety and criminal damage to property.  Motion granted.
On count 2, operate firearm while intoxicated, the defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for ninety (90) days, under the Huber Law, commencing on 06-26-16 at 5:00 p.m.
$280.00 court costs imposed, to be paid by 07-10-16 or 5 days county jail for failure to pay.
The defendant has credit for 2 days.
On counts 4 and 5, criminal damage to property and disorderly conduct; sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) No contact with the victim, Manuel Escobar;
2) Maintain fulltime employment or job search;
3) Pay court costs;
4) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
5) maintain absolute sobriety;
6) AODA assessment and follow through;
7) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
8) Provide DNA sample.  (The court imposes only one DNA surcharge).
If the agent recommends early discharge from probation, the Court may consider it.
Minutes.
